        <section id="faq-details">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="page-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
                <h2 class="page-subtitle">Your Questions, Answered</h2>

                <div class="faq-accordion">
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
                        <summary>How do I patch the game? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Follow the instructions provided <a href="https://romhackstudios.github.io/pages/howtopatch.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.15s;">
                        <summary>Pokemon keep 'getting away' when I use the Dexnav? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>You must hold the 'A' button to walk slowly. Running will scare the PokÃ©mon away, so sneak up on it carefully.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
                        <summary>How do trade evolutions work? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Visit the helpful man in Devon Corp. He will trade your PokÃ©mon and then trade it right back to trigger its evolution.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.25s;">
                        <summary>How do I use Mega Evolution? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Obtain the Mega Ring from your PC at home, give a Mega Stone to a compatible PokÃ©mon, and in battle, press 'Fight', then 'Start', and choose your move.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.3s;">
                        <summary>How do I use Z-Moves? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Acquire the Z-Ring from your father, give a Z-Crystal to a compatible PokÃ©mon, and in battle, press 'Fight', then 'Start', and pick your move.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.35s;">
                        <summary>Where can I find a specific PokÃ©mon? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Please refer to the "Wild Encounters" document included in the original game download to locate specific PokÃ©mon.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.4s;">
                        <summary>How do I use Mystery Gift? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Go to the second floor of any PokÃ©mon Center and talk to the man on the left. Ensure you save before using a code and check for correct typing.</p></div>
                    </details>
                     <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.45s;">
                        <summary>Where do I get the EXP Share? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>After delivering the letter to Steven for Mr. Stone, return to Mr. Stone in Devon Corp to receive the Exp. Share.</p></div>
                    </details>
                     <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.5s;">
                        <summary>How do I shiny hunt effectively? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Increase your chances of encountering a shiny PokÃ©mon by creating an encounter 'chain' using the DexNav. Each successful encounter in the chain boosts the odds.</p></div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item" style="animation-delay: 0.55s;">
                        <summary>Where are the new legendaries? <span class="plus-icon">+</span></summary>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><p>You must capture Hoopa first, which is a roaming encounter after the 5th badge. Once a day, Hoopa may open a portal while you're adventuring, summoning Ultra Beasts and other legendaries.</p></div>
                    </details>
                </div>
